==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonane
<hw>Non"ane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>nonus</ets>
ninth.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a group of metameric
hydrocarbons <chform>C9H20</chform> of the paraffin series; -- so called
because of the nine carbon atoms in the molecule. <stype>Normal
nonane</stype> is a colorless volatile liquid, an ingredient of ordinary
kerosene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonappearance</ent>⟦br⟧
